         <div type="traslation">
            <head>Translation</head>
            <p>As he began to copy (tutaṅki eḻuti vara) the Kācikāṇṭam, which is the poem of
               Kācivicuvaṉātacuvāmiyār, thanks to [Kācivicuvaṉātacuvāmiyār’s] benevolent
               side-glances, [the Kācikāṇṭam] was completed – first thing (mutal āka) – on the
               auspicious (puṇṇiya-) day in which occur the year 1739, the month of Vāykāci, the
               11th day, the day of Thursday, the constellation of Cōti, the thirteenth day of the
               [bright] fortnight (pakkam, i.e. pakṣam), the mukirttam of Riḻapa (i.e.
               riṣapa-mukurttam) and the vēḷai of Irāṣcata (i.e. irāṭcaca-vēḷai).</p>
         </div>
